The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, May 15: Punj Lloyd Ltd has entered into a joint venture with the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia to form a company with a share capital of two million Saudi Riyals. Punj Lloyd would own 49 per cent of the company, while 51 per cent stake would be held by Khalid Bin Bandar Bin Sultan (KBS) of Saudi Arabia. The company will be named Dayim Punj Lloyd Engineering Ltd.

 New Delhi, May 13: Parliament today amended the Companies Act, 1956, to ensure secure e-filing and authentication of documents through digital signature certificates (DSCs). This would pave the way for the implementation of MCA21, an e-governance initiative by the ministry of company affairs. 

 Calcutta, May 15: About 42 Dunlop employees, assigned maintenance work at the Sahagunj factory, today refused to work to protest against the new management under P.K. Ruia. The employees? union might even go for indefinite strike, sources said.

 Mumbai, May 15: Wockhardt Ltd has received USFDA approval for marketing the antibiotic Ceftriaxone sodium injection in the US.

 Mumbai, May 15: Lupin Ltd has signed a licensing agreement with Italian pharmaceutical company Italfarmaco for marketing its cardiovascular critical care product in the Indian market.




